The sun was found to be governed by the same basic principles as other stars: the only factors driving its activity within the system were its luminosity and its rotation.
Light intensity and rotation are combined to calculate a star's Rossby number, linked to plasma flow.
The lower the Rossby number, the lower the activity of the star in relation to its magnetic reversals.
