The Iraq Study Group issued its report today at 12:00 GMT.
He warns that no one can give guarantees that any Iraqi action at this point will stop sectarian fighting, rising violence or a tilt toward chaos.
The report begins with a call for open debate and consensus building in the United States about Middle East policies.
The report is highly critical of virtually every aspect of current executive branch policy in Iraq, and calls for an immediate change of direction.
It contains 78 recommendations, of which number one is the adoption of a new initiative before the end of the year with the purpose of protecting Iraq's borders from hostile operations and to restore diplomatic ties with its neighbors.
