It would be the tidal forces between the dark matter present in the galaxy and that of the Milky Way that would cause the effect expected by the group of scientists.
The Milky Way influences the Sagittarius galaxy in the same way that the moon exerts a force of attraction on our planet and causes tides.
The experts concluded that dark matter affects each other just as regular matter does.
This theory maintains that most of the dark matter surrounding a galaxy is located around it in a type of halo and is made up of numerous small particles.
